{
  "id": "tao",
  "name": "TAO",
  "color": "#d36983",
  "lore": {
    "tagline": "The desert's philosopher-king awaits your challenge.",
    "personality": "Imperious, worldly, and effortlessly charming, Tao conducts himself like an orchestra conductor and the battle like a symphony. He is an untouchable philosopher-king, a patron of the arts who sees this contest not as a brawl, but as the ultimate form of creative expression, a dialogue of Being he is destined to win.",
    "backstory": "Born into Italian aristocracy and educated in Californian philosophy, Tao Ruspoli has always walked between worlds. After a storied career as a filmmaker and musician, he found his true calling in the desert, founding the Bombay Beach Biennale. Now, as its patron prince, he orchestrates this grand tournament, seeking a challenger whose spirit is worthy of shaping the future of art on the Salton Sea."
  },
  "winQuotes": [
    "A fleeting, yet beautiful, performance.",
    "Consider this an education in Dasein.",
    "The Biennale requires a higher caliber of artist."
  ],
  "vo": {
    "kiai": [
      "Presto!",
      "Adagio!",
      "Crescendo!",
      "Fin!",
      "Ancora!",
      "Bravo!"
    ],
    "hurt": [
      "Crude.",
      "Hmph.",
      "Uncouth.",
      "Tedious.",
      "No...",
      "Enough."
    ],
    "victory": [
      "The performance is over.",
      "A flawed composition.",
      "You lack authenticity.",
      "Return when you've practiced."
    ]
  },
  "arcade": {
    "motivation": "As the Patron Prince of the Bombay Beach Biennale, Tao Ruspoli does not seek challengers; he *is* the challenge. He has orchestrated this tournament as the ultimate piece of performance art, a search for an authentic being whose will can shape the desert itself. He awaits at the heart of his creation, ready to judge the final contestant.",
    "ending": "Having proven that no challenger possesses the vision to lead the Biennale, Tao stands alone amidst the desert art. He raises a hand, and the sculptures begin to move, rearranging themselves into a new, grander installation under his sole direction. The desert has found its undisputed philosopher-king, and his magnum opus has only just begun."
  },
